value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a cholecystokinin stimulus.

Binding to telomeric G-quadruplex DNA structures, in which groups of four guanines adopt a flat, cyclic Hoogsteen hydrogen-bonding arrangement known as a guanine tetrad. The stacking of guanine tetrads results in G-quadruplex DNA structures in telomeres.
That part of the growth cone which represents the distal part of the structure.
That part of the lamellipodium which represents the distal part of the structure.

label.value: retrograde transporter complex, Golgi to ER

value.value: Transporter complex that recognises, binds and returns endoplasmic reticulum (ER) resident proteins that have trafficked to Golgi compartments. Targets proteins lacking the HDEL motif recognised by COPI-coated vesicles.

definition.value: An example of this is ERV41 in Saccharomyces cerevisiae (Q04651) in PMID:16093310 (inferred from direct assay).

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neuroblast migration.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neuroblast migration.
Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neuroblast migration.
A process in which a calcium ion is transported from one side of a Golgi membrane to the other by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label.value: endoplasmic reticulum stress-induced pre-emptive quality control

value.value: The response to endoplasimic reticulum stress in which nascent proteins are degraded by attenuation of their translocation into the ER followed by rerouting to the cytosol without cleavage of the signal peptide, and subsequent degradation by the proteasome.
Facilitating the opening of the ring structure of the PCNA complex, or any of the related sliding clamp complexes, and their removal from the DNA duplex, driven by ATP hydrolysis.

Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a 1-(3,5-dichloro-2,6-dihydroxy-4-methoxyphenyl)pentan-1-one stimulus.
Catalysis of the transfer of tubulin dimers to the plus end of a microtubule. The reaction is reversible depending on the availability of dimers.
The controlled release of molecules that form the basement membrane, including carbohydrates and glycoproteins by a cell.

label.value: polarized secretion of basement membrane proteins in epithelium

value.value: The basement membrane constituent secretion in which there is a restriction or targeting of basement membrane proteins for controlled release on the basal side of polarized epithelium.
The mitotic spindle organization process by which a mitotic spindle becomes asymmetric either in position or structure.
The orderly movement of a hepatic stellate cell from one site to another.

label.value: regulation of hepatic stellate cell migration

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hepatic stellate cell migration.

label.value: positive regulation of hepatic stellate cell migration

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of hepatic stellate cell migration.

label.value: negative regulation of hepatic stellate cell migration

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of hepatic stellate cell migration.
The actin filament-based process in which cytoplasmic actin filaments slide past one another resulting in contraction of a hepatic stellate cell.

label.value: regulation of hepatic stellate cell contraction

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hepatic stellate cell contraction.

label.value: positive regulation of hepatic stellate cell contraction

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of hepatic stellate cell contraction.

label.value: negative regulation of hepatic stellate cell contraction

value.value: Any process that modulates stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of hepatic stellate cell contraction.

label.value: regulation of anterograde axonal transport of mitochondrion

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of mitochondria along microtubules in axons away from the cell body and towards the presynapse.

label.value: positive regulation of anterograde axonal transport of mitochondrion

value.value: Any process that activates or increasesthe frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of mitochondria along microtubules in axons away from the cell body and towards the presynapse.

label.value: negative regulation of anterograde axonal transport of mitochondrion

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of mitochondria along microtubules in axons away from the cell body and towards the presynapse.
A clathrin-mediated endocytosis process whereby yolk proteins are internalized and trafficked through the endocytic pathway for yolk deposition.

label.value: regulation of mini excitatory postsynaptic potential

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mini excitatory postsynaptic potential. Mini excitatory postsynaptic potential is a process that leads to a temporary increase in postsynaptic potential due to the flow of positively charged ions into the postsynaptic cell, induced by the spontaneous release of a single vesicle of an excitatory neurotransmitter into the synapse.

label.value: positive regulation of mini excitatory postsynaptic potential

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of mini excitatory postsynaptic potential. Mini excitatory postsynaptic potential is a process that leads to a temporary increase in postsynaptic potential due to the flow of positively charged ions into the postsynaptic cell, induced by the spontaneous release of a single vesicle of an excitatory neurotransmitter into the synapse.

label.value: negative regulation of mini excitatory postsynaptic potential

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of mini excitatory postsynaptic potential. Mini excitatory postsynaptic potential is a process that leads to a temporary increase in postsynaptic potential due to the flow of positively charged ions into the postsynaptic cell, induced by the spontaneous release of a single vesicle of an excitatory neurotransmitter into the synapse.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of astrocyte activation.
Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of astrocyte activation.
Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of astrocyte activation.
Binding to and responding, e.g. by conformational change, to changes in the cellular level of calcium ions (Ca2+).
Catalysis of the reaction: all-trans-retinol + 2 H+ + O2 + 2 reduced [adrenodoxin] = all-trans-3,4-didehydro retinol + 2 H2O + 2 oxidized [adrenodoxin].
Catalysis of the reaction: all-trans-retinal + 2 H+ + O2 + 2 reduced [adrenodoxin] = all-trans-3,4-didehydro retinal + 2 H2O + 2 oxidized [adrenodoxin].
Catalysis of the reaction: all-trans-retinoic acid + 2 H+ + O2 + 2 reduced [adrenodoxin] = all-trans-3,4-didehydro retinoic acid + 2 H2O + 2 oxidized [adrenodoxin].
Catalysis of the reaction: 11-cis-retinal + 2 H+ + O2 + 2 reduced [adrenodoxin] = 11-cis-3,4-didehydro-retinal + 2 H2O + 2 oxidized [adrenodoxin].
A change in morphology and behavior of a glial cell resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor.
Any process in which an autophagosome is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within the cell.

label.value: negative regulation of AMPA receptor activity

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of AMPA glutamate receptor activity.
A disk-like structure that expands, rounds up into a cup-shaped structure, and eventually closes around its cargo (for example cytoplasmic components) to become an autophagosome or Cvt vesicle.

The process in which autophagosomes, double-membraned vesicles containing cytoplasmic material, fuse with a vacuole (yeast) or lysosome (e.g. mammals and insects). In the case of yeast, inner membrane-bounded structures (autophagic bodies) appear in the vacuole. Fusion provides an acidic environment and digestive function to the interior of the autophagosome.
The process in which an autophagosome fuses with an endosome to create an intermediate autophagic organelle called amphisome.

The process in which amphisomes fuse with a vacuole (yeast) or lysosome (e.g. mammals and insects). In the case of yeast, inner membrane-bounded structures (autophagic bodies) appear in the vacuole. Fusion provides an acidic environment and digestive function to the interior of the amphisome.

label.value: positive regulation of growth plate cartilage chondrocyte proliferation

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of chondrocytes in a growing endochondral bone, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.

label.value: negative regulation of growth plate cartilage chondrocyte proliferation

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of chondrocytes in a growing endochondral bone, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.

label.value: leading edge of axonal growth cone

value.value: That part of the axonal growth cone which represents the distal part of the structure.

label.value: leading edge of dendritic growth cone

value.value: That part of the dendritic growth cone which represents the distal part of the structure.
